casebody.data:
Denisha A. HARRIGAN, Appellant,
v.
The STATE of Florida, Appellee. No. 3D19-327 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Third District. Opinion filed April 10, 2019 Denisha A. Harrigan, in proper person. Ashley Moody, Attorney General, for appellee. Before EMAS, C.J., and SCALES and LINDSEY, JJ. PER CURIAM.

Affirmed. See Fla. R. Crim. P. 3.801(b) (providing: "No motion shall be filed or considered pursuant to this rule if filed more than 1 year after the sentence becomes final."); Bryant v. State , 240 So.3d 55 (Fla. 3d DCA 2018).
